title: For Sale:  Custom Tactical AR15 6.8mm SPC w Scope & Extras NICE
postcontent: Selling my custom AR15 that is chambered for 6.8mm SPC. Rifle started as a complete Bushmaster XM15-E2S 6.8mm SPC lower, changed out the handgrip for a CAA rubberized grip, the upper is a generic A3 upper with no dust cover or forward assist to keep the rifle looking smooth and clean, the handle on the top is also a removeable add on with built in hard sight and removeable scope mount. The butt stock is an Ace LTD fixed skeleton style with nice padding and a tacticalsprings.com heavy buffer spring and extra heavy buffer inside. The barrel is a Stag arms 16" medium barrel and also included the muzzle break and combination front sight/gas block. The forward stock is a UTG aluminum quad rail currently holding a magpul grip. Internally there is a LWRC 6.8mm SPC combat bolt and firing pin as well as a generic 3-9x 40mm scope to round it all off. I built it about a year ago and since then have never had a chance to shoot it. The rifle will also include 2 metal 25 round magazines, the original stag arms forward stock and hardware, original bushmaster handgrip, original spring and buffer, an extra gas tube and the 2 6.8 dummy rounds i got for it. Action works very well, spring is super strong and it takes some effort to cock the gun but the combination of the heavy buffer and spring plus the LWRC combat bolt makes it feel nice and smooth. Rifle has no issues loading the dummy rounds into the barrel or ejecting them and firing pin lines up and strikes good. And not that i know why but if anyone was so inclined the lower and bulk of the parts are standard and the gun could easily be converted to a standard .223/556 with just a couple parts. Please contact me with any questions or for more pictures.
